data.title: Jim Stewart, co-founder of Stax Records in Memphis, dies at age 92
data.meta_description: The white Tennessee farm boy and fiddle player co-founded the influential record label with his sister in a Black, inner-city Memphis neighborhood and helped build the soulful "Memphis sound."
